
Hexenwail - a modern Hexen II source port
==========================================

https://github.com/hexenwail/hexenwail

Hexenwail is a modern source port of Raven Software's Hexen II,
targeting Linux and Windows with SDL3 and OpenGL 4.3. It is based on
Hammer of Thyrion (uHexen2) by O. Sezer, which descends from the
Anvil of Thyrion Linux port by Dan Olson and Clément Bourdarias.

Hexen II was created by Raven Software Corp., published by Id Software
Inc and distributed by Activision, Inc. Hexenwail is *not* made, and
is *not* supported by any of these companies.

This code is released under the GNU Public License v2 (see COPYING).


Features
--------

* Support for Hexen II, Hexen II demo, and Portal of Praevus.
* Linux and Windows (SDL3 + OpenGL 4.3 core profile).
* OpenGL 4.3 rendering: 6 GLSL 4.30 shaders, zero fixed-function GL,
  software matrix stack, shader-based fog, VBO/SSBO alias models.
* Render scale, FOV slider, FPS cap, Show FPS toggle.
* BSP2 map format support. Widescreen Hor+ FOV scaling.
* Options reorganized into Display, Sound, and Game submenus.
* Music: OGG, MP3, Opus, FLAC, WAV, tracker (MOD/S3M/XM/IT/UMX),
  and MIDI. All codecs enabled by default.
* Colored lights, anisotropic filtering, translucent console.
* Fully network-compatible with Raven's 1.11 Windows version.
* Same binary handles base game and mission pack.
* Per-demo configuration files (see DEMO_CONFIG.md).
* Full user directories (~/.hexen2) for saves and config.


Changes from upstream uHexen2 v1.5.10
--------------------------------------

* Platform consolidated to SDL3 + OpenGL 4.3 only
* All legacy backends removed (DOS, Win32/WGL, Amiga, OS/2, macOS,
  Haiku, software renderer, HexenWorld)
* GLSL 4.30 core shaders replacing all immediate-mode GL
* Software matrix stack replacing hardware matrix stack
* VBO/SSBO-based alias model rendering with static shadedots
* Options reorganized into submenus
* Render scale, FOV slider, FPS cap
* Music defaults to All Codecs
* WASM/WebGL2 experimental build support

For the full changelog, see: git log


================================================================


1. INSTALLATION
---------------

1.1 Getting Started

Hexen II source and Hexenwail are free, but the game data is not:
you need an original copy from Raven Software / Activision, or use
the demo version (our demo packages include everything needed).

For the retail version, copy pak0.pak and pak1.pak from your cdrom
into the "data1" directory. Run "h2patch" to update to v1.11.

   c9675191e75dd25a3b9ed81ee7e05eff  data1/pak0.pak
   c2ac5b0640773eed9ebe1cda2eca2ad0  data1/pak1.pak

For Portal of Praevus, copy pak3.pak into the "portals" directory.

   77ae298dd0dcd16ab12f4a68067ff2c3  portals/pak3.pak

Game binaries:

   glhexen2  -  Linux
   glh2.exe  -  Windows


1.2 Windows Installation

Install Hexen II from your cdrom and apply the 1.11 patch (ph2v111.exe
from http://www.gamers.org/pub/idgames2/hexen2/official/patch/).

NOTE: Delete any opengl32.dll the installer puts in the game folder —
it's a 3dfx minidriver that causes "glide2x.dll not found" errors.

Extract the Hexenwail package into the installation folder. The old
h2mp.exe and glh2mp.exe are obsolete and can be deleted. To play the
mission pack: glh2 -portals


1.3 Running the Game

    cd /home/myname/hexen2
    ./glhexen2 [options]

Starts in windowed mode by default. Use -f for fullscreen, -portals
for the mission pack.

Command-line switches:

 -portals | -h2mp       Portal of Praevus mission pack
 -f | -fullscreen       Start fullscreen
 -w | -window           Start windowed
 -width N               Screen width
 -height N              Screen height (use with -width)
 -conwidth N            HUD/text scale (smaller = bigger text, 640 sanest)
 -nomouse               Disable mouse
 -nojoy                 Disable joystick
 -heapsize N            Memory to allocate (KB)
 -fsaa N                Anti-aliasing samples (0, 2, 4)
 -sndspeed N            Audio sample rate (22050, 44100, etc.)
 -nocdaudio             Disable CD music
 -nomidi                Disable MIDI
 -s | -nosound          No sound
 -nolan                 Disable networking
 -listen N              Multiplayer with max N players
 -protocol N            Server protocol (18=old 1.11, 19=default)
 -port N                Network port (default: 26900)
 -developer             Developer mode
 -condebug              Log console output
 -v | -version          Show version
 -h | -help             Show help


1.4 Sound and Music

Audio uses SDL3. The default music type is "All Codecs", searching:
OGG, Opus, MP3, FLAC, WAV, tracker (IT/S3M/XM/MOD), then MIDI.

See README.music for setting up external music files.


1.5 Networking / Multiplayer

Fully compatible with Raven's Hexen II 1.11. To let 1.11 clients
connect to a Hexenwail server, start with "-protocol 18".


1.6 Game Saves and Configuration

Stored under ~/.hexen2 (Linux) or the game directory (Windows).
  Hexen II:       ~/.hexen2/data1
  Mission Pack:   ~/.hexen2/portals
  Demo:           ~/.hexen2demo


1.7 Fullscreen/Windowed and Mouse

ALT+Enter toggles fullscreen/windowed. CTRL+G grabs/ungrabs mouse.
Resolution and mouse settings are also in the menu.


1.8 Joystick (gamepad)

Supported through SDL. Set "joystick 1" in console to enable.
Use -nojoy to disable probing entirely.

Axis mapping (set via console, -1 = none):
  joy_axisside (0), joy_axisforward (1), joy_axisyaw (2),
  joy_axispitch (3), joy_axisup (-1)

Per-axis deadzone and sensitivity cvars also available
(joy_deadzone*, joy_sensitivity*).


================================================================


2. CONSOLE VARIABLES
--------------------

fov_adapt        0/1    Hor+ FOV scaling (default: 1)
_snd_mixahead    0.1-0.9  Sound latency vs performance
snow_active      0-255  Snow multiplier (0 = none)

OpenGL:
  gl_texturemode           GL_NEAREST / GL_LINEAR /
                           GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_NEAREST (default) /
                           GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_LINEAR (trilinear)
  gl_texturemode_anisotropy  1=off, >=2 enables anisotropic
  gl_coloredlight  0/1/2  Static colored lights (0=white default)
  gl_colored_dynamic_lights 0/1  Colored dlights
  gl_extra_dynamic_lights   0/1  Extra dlights


================================================================


3. MODS
-------

    ./glhexen2 -game fo4d
    ./glhexen2 -portals -game somemod

Notable mods:
  Fortress of Four Doors - fo4d.zip
  Game of Tomes - https://github.com/cabbruzzese/gameoftomes/wiki
  Project Peanut - http://www.geocities.ws/shanjaq/index.html

Mods require the full retail version (not demo).


================================================================


4. KNOWN ISSUES
---------------

* Dedicated server coop: skull wizards may become non-solid after
  blinking, Dark Pharaoh's staff may disappear, save loading buggy.
  Does not occur with "glhexen2 -dedicated".

* Shadows are broken and disabled by default.


